{
 "name": "RPlog_Serenella_and_Shael-The_Trial",
 "title": "Serenella and Shael: The Trial",
 "summary": "In the High Court of New Alderaan, Serenella Jordain stands trial for second-degree assault before Judge Appel and a jury including Raxis, Tak Dagon, Gene, and Wrista. Prosecutor Jak M'koy paints her as an out-of-control spice addict, calling the smuggler Shael Winters, who testifies that a drugged Serenella attacked her over a cargo of cooling-unit parts, and Lieutenant Vengan Draelis, who presents the security footage. Serenella's flustered Toydarian lawyer Tryno mounts a defense of grief and possible unwitting drugging, painting Shael as projecting a family addiction issue, and puts the mourning widow on the stand. The strategy backfires spectacularly when Serenella's emotional outbursts and M'koy's revelation of her kissing another man at the Cat's Claw Cantina undercut her widow's grief, and after closing arguments the judge sends the jury to deliberate her guilt and possible sentence.",
